Seismic data acquired by Observatoire Sismologique d’Ile-de-France (OSIDF) holdings of an earthquake cluster that occurred beneath the ocean’s floor 200 kilometers southwest of the Ha’apai group of islands off the east coast of the island of Tongatapu were analyzed for further details. Three earthquakes were detected during this process. The figure below displays what earthquakes we’ve analyzed from this earthquake swarm. These earthquakes were all located beneath the floor of the Tonga Trench at a focal depth of 132.7 ± 0.3 km and a maximum focal depth of 140 km. Pay attention Cu!
